#. [race], id=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:21
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:22
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:23
msgid "race^Athvari"
msgstr "Athvari"

#. [race], id=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The Athvari are an ancient bloodline of the race of men, that are able to "
"use magic by birth, while their non-athvari counterparts have to study hard "
"in order to use magic. But even in case a man studies his whole life, he can "
"never reach the same level as an Athvari. The Athvari have sworn to protect "
"the lands of the sulthanate as they enforce the Law, which prohibits the use "
"of magic, since it has lead to severe catastrophes in the desert realms. "
"Nowadays, there are only a few Athvari left."
msgstr ""
"Los athvari son un antiguo linaje de la raza humana que pueden usar magia de "
"nacimiento, mientras que sus contrapartes no athvari deben estudiar "
"arduamente para usar magia. Pero incluso si un hombre estudia toda su vida, "
"nunca podrá alcanzar el mismo nivel que un athvari. Los athvari han jurado "
"proteger las tierras del sultanato mientras imponen la Ley, que prohíbe el "
"uso de la magia, ya que ha causado catástrofes graves en los reinos del "
"desierto. Hoy en día, solo quedan unos pocos athvari."

#. [race], id=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:31
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:32
msgid "race^Afariyat"
msgstr "Afariyat"

#. [race], id=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:33
msgid "race^Afariyaten"
msgstr "Afariyaten"

#. [race], id=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Afariyat are hexed genies that inhabit the depths below the sand and as "
"such, they seemingly emerge from dust and sands. Most weapons can't harm "
"them, yet there have not been many experience made, as afariyaten are able "
"to petrify their enemy with a simple touch. They hate genie by heart."
msgstr ""
"Los afariyat son genios malditos que habitan las profundidades bajo la arena "
"y, como tal, parecen surgir del polvo y las arenas. La mayoría de las armas "
"no pueden dañarlos, pero no hay muchas experiencias registradas, ya que los "
"afariyaten pueden petrificar a su enemigo con un simple toque. Odian a los "
"genios con todo su ser."

#. [race], id=genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:41
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:42
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:43
msgid "race^Genie"
msgstr "Genio"

#. [race], id=genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:44
msgid ""
"Genie are magical beings that inhabited the great deserts even before men "
"arrived. They are innate friendly beings that maintain a good relationship "
"with humans. Genie helped the people of the desert to build their enormous "
"cities. When the Three Kings of K'thar abused the powers of magic, most "
"genie died, since they are susceptible to destructive magic. Only a few have "
"found a safe place - either in manmade objects, such as lamps, swords or "
"jewelry, or in men that agreed to host a genie in their mortal body. United "
"they form the mighty half-genies that are both man and genie. In the land of "
"the deserts, half-genies are not seen as bastards, in fact, they are "
"respected throughout the lands, as their union symbolises the great bond "
"between man and genie that brought forth many good things to the life of "
"both kin. Genie hate Afariyaten more than anything else."
msgstr ""
"Los genios son seres mágicos que habitaban los grandes desiertos incluso "
"antes de que llegaran los humanos. Son seres amigables por naturaleza que "
"mantienen una buena relación con los humanos. Los genios ayudaron a la gente "
"del desierto a construir sus enormes ciudades. Cuando los Tres Reyes de "
"K'thar abusaron de los poderes de la magia, la mayoría de los genios "
"murieron, ya que son susceptibles a la magia destructiva. Solo unos pocos "
"han encontrado un lugar seguro, ya sea en objetos hechos por el hombre, como "
"lámparas, espadas o joyas, o en hombres que aceptaron albergar a un genio en "
"su cuerpo mortal. Unidos forman los poderosos medios genios que son tanto "
"hombre como genio. En la tierra de los desiertos, los medios genios no son "
"vistos como bastardos; de hecho, son respetados en todas las tierras, ya que "
"su unión simboliza el gran vínculo entre hombre y genio que trajo muchas "
"cosas buenas a la vida de ambos linajes. Los genios odian a los afariyaten "
"más que a nada."

#. [race], id=half_genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:51
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:52
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:53
msgid "race^Half-Genie"
msgstr "Medio Genio"

#. [race], id=half_genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/macros/races-macro.cfg:54
msgid ""
"When the Three Kings of K'thar abused magic to extend their realm and wreak "
"havoc across the lands, most genie were destroyed due to the evil magic. "
"Feeling their near end, some genie found a safe place inside manmade "
"objects, such as lamps, swords or jewelry. Other genies, however, asked men "
"to be a host to them as men were immune to certain magic that targeted "
"genies. As a symbiosis, they form the mighty half-genies that are both man "
"and genie. In the land of the deserts, half-genies are not seen as bastards, "
"in fact, they are respected throughout the lands, as their union symbolises "
"the great bond between man and genie that brought forth many good things to "
"the life of men."
msgstr ""
"Cuando los Tres Reyes de K'thar abusaron de la magia para expandir su reino "
"y causar estragos en las tierras, la mayoría de los genios fueron destruidos "
"por la magia maligna. Sintiendo su fin cercano, algunos genios encontraron "
"un lugar seguro dentro de objetos hechos por el hombre, como lámparas, "
"espadas o joyas. Otros genios, sin embargo, pidieron a los humanos que los "
"albergaran, ya que los humanos eran inmunes a cierta magia dirigida a los "
"genios. Como simbiosis, forman los poderosos medios genios que son tanto "
"hombre como genio. En la tierra de los desiertos, los medios genios no son "
"vistos como bastardos; de hecho, son respetados en todas las tierras, ya que "
"su unión simboliza el gran vínculo entre hombre y genio que trajo muchas "
"cosas buenas a la vida de los humanos."

