#. [unit_type], id=Ascended Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/ascended_athvari.cfg:5
msgid "Ascended Athvari"
msgstr "Athvari Ascendido"

#. [unit_type], id=Ascended Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/ascended_athvari.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Ascended Athvari have unlocked the power that inherits them and control it "
"with ease. Legends say that there have not been many Athvari who have been "
"able to do so. In times of great dangers however, it is noticed, that more "
"and more Athvari uncover their true powers."
msgstr ""
"Los Athvari Ascendidos han desbloqueado el poder que heredan y lo controlan "
"con facilidad. Las leyendas dicen que no ha habido muchos Athvari que hayan "
"podido hacerlo. Sin embargo, en tiempos de grandes peligros, se nota que "
"cada vez más Athvari descubren sus verdaderos poderes."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/ascended_athvari.cfg:30
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/athvari.cfg:27
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/elder_athvari.cfg:27
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/high_athvari.cfg:29
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/lost_athvari.cfg:29
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/unforgotten_athvari.cfg:29
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/iskandar.cfg:125
msgid "berdysch"
msgstr "berdysch"

#. [unit_type], id=Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/athvari.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Athvari are the enforcers of the Law, that prohibits the use of magic inside "
"the desert lands. Given their ability to teleport, Athvari quickly overthrow "
"any person inside the desert realms that uses magic."
msgstr ""
"Los athvari son los ejecutores de la Ley que prohíbe el uso de la magia "
"dentro de las tierras del desierto. Dada su habilidad para "
"teletransportarse, los athvari rápidamente derrocan a cualquier persona "
"dentro de los reinos del desierto que usa magia."

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/elder_athvari.cfg:5
msgid "Elder Athvari"
msgstr "Athvari Anciano"

#. [unit_type], id=Elder Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/elder_athvari.cfg:19
msgid "Elder Athvari often lead small groups of lower Athvari."
msgstr ""
"Los Athvari Ancianos a menudo lideran pequeños grupos de athvari de menor "
"rango."

#. [unit_type], id=High Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/high_athvari.cfg:5
msgid "High Athvari"
msgstr "Athvari Alto"

#. [unit_type], id=High Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/high_athvari.cfg:21
msgid ""
"High Athvari are the leaders of the Athvari people and the greatest among "
"their sorcerers. Their knowledge and power assure their status as commanding "
"great respect and fear among all people of the deserts. Even kings will "
"think twice before crossing them on any matter."
msgstr ""
"Los Athvari Altos son los líderes del pueblo athvari y los más grandes entre "
"sus hechiceros. Su conocimiento y poder aseguran su estatus de comandar gran "
"respeto y miedo entre toda la gente de los desiertos. Incluso los reyes "
"pensarán dos veces antes de cruzarse con ellos en cualquier asunto."

#. [unit_type], id=Lost Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/lost_athvari.cfg:5
msgid "Lost Athvari"
msgstr "Athvari Perdido"

#. [unit_type], id=Lost Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/lost_athvari.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The Athvari have always been destined to rule over men and be a force of "
"guidance through their lives. While most Athvari bring order to men and "
"women by being an unseen advisor to their kings and queens or by directly "
"ruling in a peaceful manner, there are some Athvari that believe that chaos "
"itself inheres in men and thus true order can only be achieved by the "
"destruction of the human race or by ruling with an iron fist. They stand as "
"a living testament that even good men can follow the wrong paths."
msgstr ""
"Los athvari siempre han estado destinados a gobernar sobre los hombres y ser "
"una fuerza de guía a través de sus vidas. Mientras la mayoría de los athvari "
"traen orden a hombres y mujeres siendo un asesor invisible de sus reyes y "
"reinas o gobernando directamente de manera pacífica, hay algunos athvari que "
"creen que el caos mismo inherente en los hombres y por lo tanto el verdadero "
"orden solo puede lograrse con la destrucción de la raza humana o gobernando "
"con puño de hierro. Representan un testimonio vivo de que incluso los buenos "
"hombres pueden seguir caminos equivocados."

#. [unit_type], id=Unforgotten Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/unforgotten_athvari.cfg:5
msgid "Unforgotten Athvari"
msgstr "Athvari Inolvidable"

#. [unit_type], id=Unforgotten Athvari, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/athvari/unforgotten_athvari.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The amount of time the Three Kings of K'thar have spent on the sphere has "
"only increased their desire and need for power as well as the ambition to "
"reclaim the rule over their previous subjects and extend it far beyond. The "
"corruption of magic has made them completely unable to be reasoned with and "
"made them formidable adversaries to anyone who dares to stop their nefarious "
"plans."
msgstr ""
"La cantidad de tiempo que los Tres Reyes de K'thar han pasado en la esfera "
"solo ha aumentado su deseo y necesidad de poder, así como la ambición de "
"reclamar el dominio sobre sus anteriores súbditos y extenderlo mucho más "
"allá. La corrupción de la magia los ha hecho completamente incapaces de ser "
"razonados y los ha convertido en adversarios formidables para cualquiera que "
"se atreva a detener sus planes nefastos."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Assassin, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/assassin.cfg:17
msgid ""
"In a land of honourable fighting, where the strength of armies is mostly "
"measured by their bravery and strength, the Dune Assassin are known for "
"their ability to quickly dispatch a person with the speed of a lightning "
"bolt. Their proficiency in assassinating their targets makes sure only "
"people employing them for mischievous deeds even have a hunch of their "
"excellent techniques. This only serves to increase the horror common "
"soldiers feel at the prospect of facing a Quismat one day."
msgstr ""
"En una tierra de combate honorable, donde la fuerza de los ejércitos se mide "
"principalmente por su valentía y fuerza, los Asesinos Barján son conocidos "
"por su habilidad para despachar rápidamente a una persona con la velocidad "
"de un rayo. Su pericia en asesinar a sus objetivos asegura que solo las "
"personas que los emplean para acciones maliciosas tengan siquiera una "
"sospecha de sus excelentes técnicas. Esto solo sirve para aumentar el horror "
"que sienten los soldados comunes ante la perspectiva de enfrentarse a un "
"Quismat algún día."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Cloudlurker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/cloudlurker.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Cloudlurker"
msgstr "Acechador de Nubes Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Cloudlurker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/cloudlurker.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Dune Cloudlurker are experts at surviving and hiding in the wilderness "
"of the southern lands. Given their knowledge of the human anatomy and the "
"creatures of the deserts, the Dune Cloudlurker is able to hit the weak point "
"of any enemy with ease."
msgstr ""
"Los Acechadores de Nubes Barján son expertos en sobrevivir y esconderse en "
"la naturaleza de las tierras del sur. Dada su conocimiento de la anatomía "
"humana y las criaturas de los desiertos, el Acechador de Nubes Barján es "
"capaz de golpear el punto débil de cualquier enemigo con facilidad."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Combuster, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/combuster.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Combuster"
msgstr "Incendiario Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Combuster, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/combuster.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The study and dedication that the combuster have given to the mysterious and "
"ever lasting nature of fire availed them the tools to successfully maintain "
"and use it as devastating weapon in close quarter combat. Only caring now "
"for spreading and beholding and the flames they conjured, they have no "
"compassion for human lives neither their homes, making them feared and "
"despised not only by their enemies but often even their own comrades."
msgstr ""
"El estudio y dedicación que los incendiarios han dado a la naturaleza "
"misteriosa y eterna del fuego les proporcionó las herramientas para "
"mantenerlo y usarlo con éxito como un arma devastadora en combate cuerpo a "
"cuerpo. Ahora solo preocupados por esparcir y contemplar las llamas que "
"conjuran, no tienen compasión por las vidas humanas ni por sus hogares, lo "
"que los hace temidos y despreciados no solo por sus enemigos sino a menudo "
"incluso por sus propios compañeros."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/combuster.cfg:25
msgid "naphtha attack"
msgstr "ataque de nafta"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/combuster.cfg:37
msgid "naphta grenade"
msgstr "granada de nafta"

#. [unstore_unit]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/combuster.cfg:163
msgid "burned armour"
msgstr "armadura quemada"

#. [unstore_unit]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/combuster.cfg:164
msgid "female^burned armour"
msgstr "armadura quemada"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Greatlance, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/greatlance.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Greatlance"
msgstr "Gran Alabardero Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Greatlance, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/greatlance.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Clad in several layers of thick leather and steel armour, the Dune "
"Greatlance certainly takes up the most important task among the warriors of "
"the dunefolk. Wielding a mighty, 5 meter long pike, the Dune Greatlance is "
"the protector of the gates of the grand cities of the desert lands and is "
"able to impale aggressors even before they understand what arrives to them. "
"To proclaim the message of impregnableness, many pikes grace the outer walls "
"of the cities - with their victims still attached to them."
msgstr ""
"Vestido con varias capas de gruesa armadura de cuero y acero, el Gran "
"Alabardero Barján ciertamente ocupa la tarea más importante entre los "
"guerreros de los barjanes. Empuñando una poderosa pica de 5 metros de largo, "
"la Gran Lanza Barján es el protector de las puertas de las grandes ciudades "
"de las tierras del desierto y es capaz de empalar a los agresores incluso "
"antes de que entiendan qué les llega. Para proclamar el mensaje de "
"inexpugnabilidad, muchas picas adornan las murallas exteriores de las "
"ciudades, con sus víctimas aún adheridas a ellas."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/greatlance.cfg:27
msgid "impale"
msgstr "empalar"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Guardsman, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/guardsman.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Guardsman"
msgstr "Guardia Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Guardsman, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/guardsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The great shield of the Dune Guardsman is handed through the generations and "
"from father to son. Usually, the oldest son will be given the shield of the "
"father, either when he dies in battle or of elderness and the task to "
"protect his family and his kin is laid upon his shoulders. Dune Guardsman "
"are often the first to enter a battle and they only leave if the battle has "
"been won or the last of his comrades has successfully escaped."
msgstr ""
"El gran escudo del Guardia Barján se transmite a través de las generaciones "
"y de padre a hijo. Usualmente, al hijo mayor se le da el escudo del padre, "
"ya sea cuando muere en batalla o de vejez y la tarea de proteger a su "
"familia y su linaje recae sobre sus hombros. Los Guardias Barján a menudo "
"son los primeros en entrar en una batalla y solo se retiran si la batalla ha "
"sido ganada o el último de sus compañeros ha escapado con éxito."

#. [unit_type], id=Keshian Immortal, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/keshianimmortal.cfg:4
msgid "Keshian Immortal"
msgstr "Inmortal de Kesh"

#. [unit_type], id=Keshian Immortal, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/keshianimmortal.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Keshian Immortals are a rare caste of the warriors of the forces of "
"Kesh. These well equipped and trained warriors were given their names during "
"the times of the Great War against the three kings. During these times, the "
"Immortals were the first to fight and the last to fall. Since that time, the "
"few retreating soldiers of the people of the desert lands brought forth the "
"tales of the Immortals."
msgstr ""
"Los Inmortales de Kesh son una casta rara de los guerreros de las fuerzas de "
"Kesh. Estos guerreros bien equipados y entrenados recibieron su nombre "
"durante los tiempos de la Gran Guerra contra los tres reyes. Durante esos "
"tiempos, los Inmortales fueron los primeros en luchar y los últimos en caer. "
"Desde ese tiempo, los pocos soldados en retirada del pueblo de las tierras "
"del desierto trajeron los relatos de los Inmortales."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Mage, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/mage.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Mage"
msgstr "Mago Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Mage, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/mage.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Power is something that always has been a deep desire in most people's "
"heart.  In some, the hate and denial for the imposed dichotomy of the "
"Athvari reached a breaking point, leading people like the Dune Mage to "
"become very dangerous for their knowledge of magic among a people as "
"abrasive of the forbidden arts as the desert people."
msgstr ""
"El poder es algo que siempre ha sido un deseo profundo en el corazón de la "
"mayoría de las personas. En algunos, el odio y la negación por la dicotomía "
"impuesta de los athvari alcanzó un punto de ruptura, llevando a personas "
"como el Mago Barján a volverse muy peligrosas por su conocimiento de la "
"magia entre un pueblo tan abrasivo de las artes prohibidas como el pueblo "
"del desierto."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Palaceguard, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/palaceguard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Dune Palaceguard are a rare class of warriors whose sole purpose is to "
"protect their Dune Warmaster's life at all costs. Since their armour is said "
"to be made out of pure crystals the Dune Palaceguard are not as hard-wearing "
"as their comrades on the battlefield; yet their expertise with their heavy "
"scimitars is unmatched and they may even hit a single grain of sand floating "
"in the wind."
msgstr ""
"Los Guardias del Palacio Barján son una clase rara de guerreros cuyo único "
"propósito es proteger la vida de su Maestro de Guerra a toda costa. Dado que "
"se dice que su armadura está hecha de cristales puros, los Guardias del "
"Palacio Barján no son tan resistentes como sus compañeros en el campo de "
"batalla; sin embargo, su pericia con sus pesadas cimitarras es inigualable y "
"pueden incluso golpear un solo grano de arena flotando en el viento."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Plunderer, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/plunderer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Wielding two great scimitars, the Dune Plunderer lives in the lands south to "
"the ashland deserts."
msgstr ""
"Empuñando dos grandes cimitarras, el Saqueador Barján vive en las tierras al "
"sur de los desiertos de ceniza."

#. [swarm]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/plunderer.cfg:35
msgid ""
"The less hitpoints the Dune Plunderer has, the more attacks he gets. Up to a "
"max. of 6 attacks."
msgstr ""
"Cuanto menos puntos de vida tenga el Saqueador Barján, más ataques obtiene. "
"Hasta un máximo de 6 ataques."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Prophet, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/prophet.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Prophet"
msgstr "Profeta Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Prophet, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/prophet.cfg:18
msgid ""
"As advisors with great political power, the Dune Prophet prefer to use "
"luxurious garments and poisonous words as their weapons against foes in "
"place of brute force. Being armed with great respect and authority among its "
"peers, noticing one of them on the battlefield inspires terror in their "
"foes, as they are among the greatest dangers to any nation opposed to them."
msgstr ""
"Como asesores con gran poder político, los Profetas Barjanes prefieren usar "
"vestimentas lujosas y palabras venenosas como sus armas contra los enemigos "
"en lugar de la fuerza bruta. Armados con gran respeto y autoridad entre sus "
"pares, notar a uno de ellos en el campo de batalla inspira terror en sus "
"enemigos, ya que están entre los mayores peligros para cualquier nación "
"opuesta a ellos."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/prophet.cfg:24
msgid "ceremonial dagger"
msgstr "daga ceremonial"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Sandlurker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/sandlurker.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Sandlurker"
msgstr "Merodeador Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Sandlurker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/sandlurker.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The Dune Sandlurker are experts at surviving and hiding in the wilderness of "
"the southern lands. Given their knowledge of the human anatomy and the "
"creatures of the deserts, the Dune Sandlurker is able to hit the weak point "
"of any enemy with ease."
msgstr ""
"Los Merodeadores Barjanes son expertos en sobrevivir y esconderse en la "
"naturaleza de las tierras del sur. Dada su conocimiento de la anatomía "
"humana y las criaturas de los desiertos, el Acechador Barján es capaz de "
"golpear el punto débil de cualquier enemigo con facilidad."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Sandstalker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/sandstalker.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Sandstalker"
msgstr "Acechador Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Sandstalker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/sandstalker.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The Dune sandstalker are experts at surviving and hiding in the wilderness "
"of the southern lands. Given their knowledge of the human anatomy and the "
"creatures of the deserts, the Dune sandstalker is able to hit the weak point "
"of any enemy with ease."
msgstr ""
"Los Acechadores Barjanes son expertos en sobrevivir y esconderse en la "
"naturaleza de las tierras del sur. Dada su conocimiento de la anatomía "
"humana y las criaturas de los desiertos, el Acechador Barján es capaz de "
"golpear el punto débil de cualquier enemigo con facilidad."

#. [unit_type], id=Serrulian Sandmare, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/serruliansandmare.cfg:4
msgid "Serrulian Sandmare"
msgstr "Pesadilla de Arena de Serrul"

#. [unit_type], id=Serrulian Sandmare, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/serruliansandmare.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Sandmares are giant reptiloid creatures that roam the eastern parts of the "
"great deserts. The forces of Serrul managed to tame and breed Sandmares, "
"using only the toughest of Sandmares as their mighty and loyal steeds. In "
"spite of their size, they are still hard to see in the deserts, due to the "
"sands that they swirl up. In times of war, an approaching sandstorm may not "
"be a sandstorm - but rather a large group of Serrulian Sandmares charging at "
"their foes."
msgstr ""
"Las Pesadillas de Arena son criaturas reptiloides gigantes que vagan por las "
"partes orientales de los grandes desiertos. Las fuerzas de Serrul lograron "
"domar y criar Pesadillas de Arena, usando solo las más fuertes como sus "
"poderosos y leales corceles. A pesar de su tamaño, todavía son difíciles de "
"ver en los desiertos, debido a las arenas que levantan. En tiempos de "
"guerra, una tormenta de arena que se acerca puede no ser una tormenta de "
"arena, sino más bien un gran grupo de Pesadillas de Arena de Serrul cargando "
"contra sus enemigos."

#. [attacks]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/serruliansandmare.cfg:46
msgid "This unit ignores the retaliation of the enemy and just overruns it."
msgstr "Esta unidad ignora la represalia del enemigo y simplemente lo arrolla."

# pendiente: confirmar o cambiar nombre.
#. [unit_type], id=Dune Sharpshooter, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/sharpshooter.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Sharpshooter"
msgstr "Tirador Certero Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Sharpshooter, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/sharpshooter.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The Dune Sharpshooter are bandits that live in the deserts and tend to rob "
"caravans. They quickly move across the deserts and are hard to see."
msgstr ""
"Los Tiradores Certeros Barján son bandidos que viven en los desiertos y "
"tienden a robar caravanas. Se mueven rápidamente a través de los desiertos y "
"son difíciles de ver."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Shieldguard, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/shieldguard.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Shieldguard"
msgstr "Protector Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Shieldguard, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/shieldguard.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Dune shieldguard who have proven to defend their comrades at all costs are "
"given the rank of a Dune Shieldguard. The shield of the Dune Shieldguard is "
"then enchanted by mystical genies giving it great powers. In battle, many "
"ordinary soldiers such as the Dune Rover or Dune Soldier prefer to stay "
"close to the Dune Shieldguard, as their mighty shield is able to not only "
"protect the Dune Shieldguard himself from arrows and spears, but also "
"adjacent soldiers."
msgstr ""
"Los Protectores Barjanes que han demostrado defender a sus compañeros a toda "
"costa reciben el rango de Protector Barján. El escudo del Protector Barján "
"es entonces encantado por genios místicos dándole grandes poderes. En "
"batalla, muchos soldados ordinarios como el Caminante Barján o el Soldado "
"Barján prefieren quedarse cerca del Protector Barján, ya que su poderoso "
"escudo es capaz de no solo proteger al propio Protector Barján de flechas y "
"lanzas, sino también a soldados adyacentes."

#. [unit_type], id=Afariyat_Dune Slaughterer, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/slaughterer-afariyat.cfg:4
msgid "Afariyat-Dune Slaughterer"
msgstr "Carnicero Barján Afariyat"

#. [unit_type], id=Afariyat_Dune Slaughterer, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/slaughterer-afariyat.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The ashuar are mercenaries from the lands south to the ashland deserts. They "
"are fighting for whoever paid the highest price and often they are paid by "
"Dune Warmasters to attack their foes."
msgstr ""
"Los ashuar son mercenarios de las tierras al sur de los desiertos de ceniza. "
"Luchan por quien pague el precio más alto y a menudo son pagados por "
"Maestros de Guerra Barján para atacar a sus enemigos."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Slaughterer, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/slaughterer.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Slaughterer"
msgstr "Carnicero Barján"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Slaughterer, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/slaughterer.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Dune Slaughterer are mercenaries from the lands south to the ashland "
"deserts. They are fighting for whoever paid the highest price and often they "
"are paid by Dune Warmasters to attack their foes."
msgstr ""
"Los Carniceros Barjanes son mercenarios de las tierras al sur de los "
"desiertos de ceniza. Luchan por quien pague el precio más alto y a menudo "
"son pagados por Maestros de Guerra Barján para atacar a sus enemigos."

#. [unit_type], id=Tharwyan Yercrona, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/tharwyanyercrona.cfg:4
msgid "Th'arwyan Yer-cron'a"
msgstr "Yer-cron'a de Th'arwya"

#. [unit_type], id=Tharwyan Yercrona, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/tharwyanyercrona.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Yer-cron'ae are mystical beings that came into existence once the humans "
"arrived in the great deserts and encountered the mighty djinn that already "
"lived there. Some say, the Yer-cron'ae are the highest of the djinns, others "
"say, the Yer-cron'ae are the mergence of men and djinn, as the fusion of "
"both had been observed when the three kings started their reign. While their "
"origin is unknown to most but themselves, their magical power is known "
"throughout the lands. While leaving in the deserts themselves, no monster "
"nor natural disaster seems to harm them. It is said that they turn to grains "
"of sand when a danger approaches. During the Great War against K'thar, "
"Th'arwya recruited the mighty Yer-cron'ae to fight amongst their ranks.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tThe Yer-cron'ae refuse to take part in wars of men, but this time they "
"knew that it is not just men's fate that is decided in the war against the "
"three kings."
msgstr ""
"Los Yer-cron'ae son seres místicos que llegaron a existir una vez que los "
"humanos llegaron a los grandes desiertos y encontraron a los poderosos "
"genios que ya vivían allí. Algunos dicen que los Yer-cron'ae son los más "
"altos de los genios, otros dicen que los Yer-cron'ae son la fusión de "
"hombres y genios, ya que la fusión de ambos había sido observada cuando los "
"tres reyes comenzaron su reinado. Mientras su origen es desconocido para la "
"mayoría pero no para ellos mismos, su poder mágico es conocido en todas las "
"tierras. Mientras viven en los desiertos mismos, ningún monstruo ni desastre "
"natural parece dañarlos. Se dice que se convierten en granos de arena cuando "
"se acerca un peligro. Durante la Gran Guerra contra K'thar, Th'arwya reclutó "
"a los poderosos Yer-cron'ae para luchar entre sus filas.\n"
"\t\n"
"\tLos Yer-cron'ae se niegan a participar en guerras de hombres, pero esta "
"vez sabían que no solo el destino de los hombres se decide en la guerra "
"contra los tres reyes."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/tharwyanyercrona.cfg:25
msgid "touch of the Yer-Cron"
msgstr "toque del Yer-Cron"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/tharwyanyercrona.cfg:39
msgid "earth shards"
msgstr "fragmentos de tierra"

#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Breaker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_breaker.cfg:4
msgid "Wyvern Breaker"
msgstr "Domador de Guivernos"

#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Breaker, race=dunefolk
#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Linebreaker, race=dunefolk
#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Rider, race=dunefolk
#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Siegebreaker, race=dunefolk
#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_breaker.cfg:19
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_linebreaker.cfg:19
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_rider.cfg:21
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_siegebreaker.cfg:19
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/wyvern.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Wyverns are agile dragon-like creatures that inhabit the east of the "
"vastness of the ashland desert. Since a long time, wyverns pose as a "
"valuable trophy to the warriors of the dunefolk, yet only the bravest and "
"strongest are able to overwhelm a wyvern and out of them, only the fewest of "
"the few may train a wyvern. "
msgstr ""
"Los guivernos son criaturas ágiles parecidas a dragones que habitan al este "
"de la vastedad del desierto de ceniza. Desde hace mucho tiempo, los "
"guivernos representan un valioso trofeo para los guerreros de los barjanes, "
"sin embargo solo los más valientes y fuertes son capaces de dominar a un "
"guiverno y de ellos, solo los menos de los menos pueden entrenar a un "
"guiverno."

#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Linebreaker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_linebreaker.cfg:4
msgid "Wyvern Linebreaker"
msgstr "Rompefilas de Guiverno"

#. [unit_type], id=Wyvern Siegebreaker, race=dunefolk
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/dunefolk/wyvern_siegebreaker.cfg:4
msgid "Wyvern Siegebreaker"
msgstr "Rompeasedios de Guiverno"

#. [unit_type], id=Elvish Bloodmaiden, race=elf
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/elves/bloodmaiden.cfg:4
msgid "Elvish Bloodmaiden"
msgstr "Doncella de Sangre Elfa"

#. [unit_type], id=Elvish Bloodmaiden, race=elf
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/elves/bloodmaiden.cfg:18
msgid ""
"For many races, it is highly unlikely to send their females into battle. For "
"certain elvish populations however, females called 'bloodmaiden' are sent "
"into battle as a rearguard whenever the elvish army suffered huge losses. "
"Only equipped with a long skirt and a sharp sword, the bloodmaidens then "
"blindly search for the ones that harmed their kin, finding them and turning "
"the battlefield into a pool of blood."
msgstr ""
"Para muchas razas, es muy improbable enviar a sus hembras a la batalla. Sin "
"embargo, para ciertas poblaciones elfas, hembras llamadas «doncellas de "
"sangre» son enviadas a la batalla como retaguardia cada vez que el ejército "
"elfo sufre grandes pérdidas. Equipadas solo con una falda larga y una espada "
"afilada, las doncellas de sangre luego buscan ciegamente a los que dañaron a "
"su gente, encontrándolos y convirtiendo el campo de batalla en un charco de "
"sangre."

#. [unit_type], id=Elvish Vengeance, race=elf
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/elves/vengeance.cfg:4
msgid "Elvish Vengeance"
msgstr "Venganza Elfa"

#. [unit_type], id=Elvish Vengeance, race=elf
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/elves/vengeance.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A bloodmaiden's eyes are covered up as she has an inner connection with the "
"fairy world that grants her new senses. Having now achieved a great bond "
"with the fairy world, though not the way the sylphs do, the fairy world now "
"tries to break through the body of the bloodmaiden, and she is becoming the "
"ones called vengeance."
msgstr ""
"Los ojos de una doncella de sangre están cubiertos ya que tiene una conexión "
"interna con el mundo feérico que le otorga nuevos sentidos. Habiendo logrado "
"ahora un gran vínculo con el mundo feérico, aunque no de la forma en que lo "
"hacen las sílfides, el mundo feérico ahora intenta atravesar el cuerpo de la "
"doncella de sangre, y ella se está convirtiendo en las llamadas venganza."

#. [unit_type], id=Apparition, race=elf, gender=female
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/apparition.cfg:4
msgid "Apparition"
msgstr "Aparición"

#. [unit_type], id=Apparition, race=elf, gender=female
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/apparition.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Once being an adventurous elf roaming the desert lands in the search of so "
"called moon crystals, Au'la encountered the Sphere, the magical construct of "
"the Athvari, when it wrested free from their hands. The Sphere served as an "
"arcane prison that prohibits the use of magic of the imprisoned ones. Yet "
"the three great mages that had been locked inside its dimensions had been "
"able to overcome the magical barriers and cast forth their desastrous magic "
"from inside. During the direct encounter with the Sphere, harmful magic "
"known to destroy life with ease had been casted from within. Au'la, however, "
"was not influenced by it. Instead, the magic set free her inner magical "
"powers and turned into a pure magical being. It is said, that the moon "
"crystals protected her from the harmful magic. Being a transcended form, "
"swords and pikes can't harm her and she can even absorb the life power of "
"her enemies. While she is not an inherently evil creatuer, her foes fear "
"her, because she can make the bodies of her enemies implode with raw force."
msgstr ""
"Una vez siendo una elfa aventurera que vagaba por las tierras del desierto "
"en busca de los llamados cristales lunares, Au'la encontró la Esfera, la "
"construcción mágica de los athvari, cuando se liberó de sus manos. La Esfera "
"servía como una prisión arcana que prohíbe el uso de la magia de los "
"aprisionados. Sin embargo, los tres grandes magos que habían sido encerrados "
"dentro de sus dimensiones habían podido superar las barreras mágicas y "
"lanzar su magia desastrosa desde adentro. Durante el encuentro directo con "
"la Esfera, magia dañina conocida por destruir la vida con facilidad había "
"sido lanzada desde adentro. Au'la, sin embargo, no fue influenciada por "
"ella. En cambio, la magia liberó sus poderes mágicos internos y se convirtió "
"en un ser puramente mágico. Se dice que los cristales lunares la protegieron "
"de la magia dañina. Siendo una forma trascendida, espadas y picas no pueden "
"dañarla y ella puede incluso absorber el poder vital de sus enemigos. Aunque "
"no es una criatura inherentemente malvada, sus enemigos la temen, porque "
"puede hacer que los cuerpos de sus enemigos implosionen con fuerza bruta."

#. [advancement], id=amla_aula_MAX_stardust
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:8
msgid "Stardust"
msgstr "Polvo de Estrellas"

#. [advancement], id=amla_aula_MAX_stardust
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:9
msgid ""
"    grants the stardust special: reduces the attacker's number of strikes by "
"1."
msgstr ""
"    otorga la especialidad polvo de estrellas: reduce el número de golpes "
"del atacante en 1."

#. [advancement], id=amla_aula_MAX_implosion
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:32
msgid "Implosion"
msgstr "Implosión"

#. [advancement], id=amla_aula_MAX_implosion
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:33
msgid "    grants a strong area of effect attack with a low chance to hit."
msgstr ""
"    otorga un fuerte ataque de área de efecto con baja probabilidad de "
"acertar."

#. [dummy], id=AULA_implosion
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:50
msgid "implosion"
msgstr "implosión"

#. [dummy], id=AULA_implosion
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:51
msgid ""
"A powerful but unreliable area-of-effect attack. It has a low chance to hit, "
"but if successful, it deals additionally 10 arcane lawful damage to all all "
"adjacent units, except Aula."
msgstr ""
"Un ataque poderoso pero poco confiable de área de efecto. Tiene baja "
"probabilidad de acertar, pero si tiene éxito, inflige adicionalmente 10 de "
"daño arcano legal a todas las unidades adyacentes, excepto Aula."

#. [advancement], id=amla_aula_MAX_idol_of_the_Sphere
#. [idol_of_the_sphere]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:63
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:73
msgid "Idol of the Sphere"
msgstr "Ídolo de la Esfera"

#. [advancement], id=amla_aula_MAX_idol_of_the_Sphere
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:64
msgid "    grants +1 hp per kill."
msgstr "    otorga +1 punto de vida por muerte."

#. [idol_of_the_sphere]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:74
msgid ""
"Absorbs the energy of the defeated enemy unit and permanently gains +1 hp."
msgstr ""
"Absorbe la energía de la unidad enemiga derrotada y gana permanentemente +1 "
"punto de vida."

#. [unit_type], id=Aula, race=elf, gender=female
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:84
msgid "The Descendant of the Sphere"
msgstr "La Descendiente de la Esfera"

#. [unit_type], id=Aula, race=elf, gender=female
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/aula.cfg:99
msgid ""
"Once being an adventurous elf roaming the desert lands in the search of so "
"called moon crystals, Au'la encountered the Sphere, the magical construct of "
"the flowing, when it wrested free from their hands. The Sphere served as an "
"arcane prison that prohibits the use of magic of the imprisoned ones. Yet "
"the three great mages that had been locked inside its dimensions had been "
"able to overcome the magical barriers and cast forth their disastrous magic "
"from inside. During the direct encounter with the Sphere, harmful magic "
"known to destroy life with ease had been casted from within. Au'la, however, "
"was not influenced by it. Instead, the magic set free her inner magical "
"powers and turned into a pure magical being. It is said, that the moon "
"crystals protected her from the harmful magic. Being a transcended form, "
"swords and pikes can't harm her and she can even absorb the life power of "
"her enemies. While she is not an inherently evil creature, her foes fear "
"her, because she can make the bodies of her enemies implode with raw force."
msgstr ""
"Una vez siendo una elfa aventurera que vagaba por las tierras del desierto "
"en busca de los llamados cristales lunares, Au'la encontró la Esfera, la "
"construcción mágica de los fluyentes, cuando se liberó de sus manos. La "
"Esfera servía como una prisión arcana que prohíbe el uso de la magia de los "
"aprisionados. Sin embargo, los tres grandes magos que habían sido encerrados "
"dentro de sus dimensiones habían podido superar las barreras mágicas y "
"lanzar su magia desastrosa desde adentro. Durante el encuentro directo con "
"la Esfera, magia dañina conocida por destruir la vida con facilidad había "
"sido lanzada desde adentro. Au'la, sin embargo, no fue influenciada por "
"ella. En cambio, la magia liberó sus poderes mágicos internos y se convirtió "
"en un ser puramente mágico. Se dice que los cristales lunares la protegieron "
"de la magia dañina. Siendo una forma trascendida, espadas y picas no pueden "
"dañarla y ella puede incluso absorber el poder vital de sus enemigos. Aunque "
"no es una criatura inherentemente malvada, sus enemigos la temen, porque "
"puede hacer que los cuerpos de sus enemigos implosionen con fuerza bruta."

