#. [unit_type], id=Iskandar, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/iskandar.cfg:97
msgid "The Remembrancer"
msgstr "El Recordador"

#. [unit_type], id=Iskandar, race=athvari
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/iskandar.cfg:115
msgid ""
"Iskandar is one of the Athvari, mystical mages from the eastern parts of the "
"Great Continent, from a land that is known as the Silver Lands. As an "
"Athvari, Iskandar was responsible for the creation of the Sphere, an arcane "
"prison, that eventually got hold of the three kings of the southern deserts. "
"Being responsible for the great order of things, the Athvari protect "
"mankind. His great powers allows him to instantly teleport to allies in "
"order to fight the evil and protect the ones he seemed worthy. Moreover, "
"Iskandar is able to sap the life energy of nearby beings, making even a "
"young soldiers as frail as the elderly."
msgstr ""
"Iskandar es uno de los athvari, magos místicos de las partes orientales del "
"Gran Continente, de una tierra conocida como las Tierras Plateadas. Como "
"athvari, Iskandar fue responsable de la creación de la Esfera, una prisión "
"arcana, que eventualmente capturó a los tres reyes de los desiertos del sur. "
"Siendo responsable del gran orden de las cosas, los athvari protegen a la "
"humanidad. Sus grandes poderes le permiten teletransportarse "
"instantáneamente a aliados para combatir el mal y proteger a aquellos que "
"consideró dignos. Además, Iskandar es capaz de absorber la energía vital de "
"seres cercanos, haciendo que incluso soldados jóvenes sean tan frágiles como "
"los ancianos."

#. [unstore_unit]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/iskandar.cfg:343
msgid "+1 damage"
msgstr "+1 daño"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Dragon, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/khazran.cfg:4
msgid "Black Dragon"
msgstr "Dragón Negro"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Dragon, race=monster
#. [unit_type], id=Undead Black Dragon, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/khazran.cfg:22
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/khazran.cfg:152
msgid ""
" Stories of Black Dragons are known to be a mere myth. Yet, these legends "
"told to little children throughout the desert contain surprising amounts of "
"details and every so often rumors of encounters with such a creature "
"circulate. Now tell me traveller, is it wise to believe in children's "
"stories? Probably not, but does this mean you should follow such a rumor to "
"its source? Walk then on the fine path between gullibility and recklessness, "
"but beware the tales end."
msgstr ""
" Las historias de Dragones Negros se conocen como un mero mito. Sin embargo, "
"estas leyendas contadas a niños pequeños a través del desierto contienen "
"cantidades sorprendentes de detalles y cada tanto circulan rumores de "
"encuentros con tal criatura. Ahora dime viajero, ¿es sabio creer en "
"historias de niños? Probablemente no, pero ¿eso significa que deberías "
"seguir tal rumor hasta su fuente? Camina entonces por el fino sendero entre "
"la credulidad y la imprudencia, pero ten cuidado con el final de las "
"historias."

#. [unit_type], id=Undead Black Dragon, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/khazran.cfg:136
msgid "Undead Black Dragon"
msgstr "Dragón Negro No-Muerto"

#. [unit_type], id=Athvari Counselor, race=athvari, gender=male
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/maralek.cfg:4
msgid "Athvari Counselor"
msgstr "Consejero Athvari"

#. [unit_type], id=Athvari Counselor, race=athvari, gender=male
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/maralek.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The mistery surroundering the Athvari and their practices has consistently "
"attracted attention to their actions. Being interested in preventing the "
"dispersion of the ways of magic and in ensuring the safety of the desert "
"people, a few of these have taken on their own hands the task to guide and "
"help the Khalids in their task of protecting their realms."
msgstr ""
"El misterio que rodea a los athvari y sus prácticas ha atraído "
"consistentemente atención a sus acciones. Estando interesados en prevenir la "
"dispersión de las formas de la magia y en asegurar la seguridad del pueblo "
"del desierto, unos pocos de estos han tomado en sus propias manos la tarea "
"de guiar y ayudar a los Khalids en su tarea de proteger sus reinos."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
