msgstr "    petrifica unidades enemigas"

#. [unit_type], id=Yrialdhe, race=monster, gender=female
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/yrialdhe.cfg:70
msgid "The Snake"
msgstr "La Serpiente"

#. [unit_type], id=Yrialdhe, race=monster, gender=female
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/yrialdhe.cfg:85
msgid ""
"Yrialdhe is a creation of the three kings of the southern deserts and served "
"as the general of the army of K'thar. During the great war, when the city "
"states of Serrul, Th'arwya and Kesh united in order to overpower K'thar, "
"Yrialdhe sent her soldiers into battle. Slithering through the enemy lines "
"with both ease and her two blades, the soldiers of the united armies fell "
"quickly, not knowing what struck them. Moreover, the faces of the petrified "
"still graze the old battlefield. One look of Yrialdhe suffices to turn a "
"heart into stone."
msgstr ""
"Yrialdhe es una creación de los tres reyes de los desiertos del sur y sirvió "
"como general del ejército de K'thar. Durante la gran guerra, cuando las "
"ciudades estado de Serrul, Th'arwya y Kesh se unieron para derrocar a "
"K'thar, Yrialdhe envió a sus soldados a la batalla. Deslizándose a través de "
"las líneas enemigas con facilidad y sus dos hojas, los soldados de los "
"ejércitos unidos caían rápidamente, sin saber qué los golpeó. Además, los "
"rostros de los petrificados todavía recorren el viejo campo de batalla. Una "
"sola mirada de Yrialdhe basta para convertir un corazón en piedra."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/heroes/yrialdhe.cfg:106
msgid "petrifying gaze"
msgstr "mirada petrificante"

#. [unit_type], id=Catapult, race=mechanical
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/mechanic/catapult.cfg:6
msgid "Catapult"
msgstr "Catapulta"

#. [unit_type], id=Catapult, race=mechanical
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/mechanic/catapult.cfg:77
msgid "Catapults are used by great armies to break down walls."
msgstr ""
"Las catapultas son usadas por grandes ejércitos para derribar murallas."

#. [unit_type], id=Afariyat, race=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/afariyat.cfg:4
msgid "Afariyat"
msgstr "Afariyat"

#. [unit_type], id=Afariyat, race=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/afariyat.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Afariyaten are hexed djinns that inhabit the depths below the sand and as "
"such, they seemingly emerge from dust and sands. Most weapons can't harm "
"them, yet there were not many encounters at which the foe of the afariyat "
"survived, as afariyaten are able to petrify their enemy with a simple touch. "
"They hate djinn by heart."
msgstr ""
"Los afariyaten son genios malditos que habitan en las profundidades bajo la "
"arena y como tal, parecen emerger del polvo y las arenas. La mayoría de las "
"armas no pueden dañarlos, sin embargo no hubo muchos encuentros en los que "
"el enemigo de los afariyat sobreviviera, ya que los afariyaten pueden "
"petrificar a su enemigo con un simple toque. Odian a los genios con todo su "
"ser."

#. [unit_type], id=Afariyat_Kabir, race=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/afariyat_kabir.cfg:4
msgid "Afariyat-Kabir"
msgstr "Afariyat-Kabir"

#. [unit_type], id=Afariyat_Kabir, race=afariyat
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/afariyat_kabir.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Afariyat-Kabir are greater afariyaten that often fight for a greater cause "
"that directly or indirectly harms their enemy, the djinn. As such, they "
"often follow warlords and trick them into doing what they want. Wielding a "
"magical scimitar, the afariyat-kabir is able to easily cut through the "
"thickest of armours."
msgstr ""
"Los Afariyat-Kabir son afariyaten mayores que a menudo luchan por una causa "
"mayor que daña directa o indirectamente a su enemigo, los genios. Como tal, "
"a menudo siguen a señores de la guerra y los engañan para que hagan lo que "
"ellos quieren. Empuñando una cimitarra mágica, el afariyat-kabir es capaz de "
"cortar fácilmente a través de las armaduras más gruesas."

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Worm, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/duneworm.cfg:4
msgid "Dune Worm"
msgstr "Gusano del Desierto"

#. [unit_type], id=Dune Worm, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/duneworm.cfg:57
msgid ""
"Duneworms or Kar'rhur-Hai as they are called in the desert lands, are huge "
"worm-like creatures that roam the ashland deserts to the south of the bay of "
"clouds. Given their huge mouth, the duneworms nourish from the sand itself, "
"digesting any living creature or organic debris that lies within. As such, "
"they are often called the 'Whales of the desert'. When getting near to their "
"nest, the duneworms are also seen to have devoured travellers that did not "
"expect their presence."
msgstr ""
"Los gusanos del desierto o Kar'rhur-Hai como se les llama en las tierras del "
"desierto, son criaturas enormes parecidas a gusanos que vagan por los "
"desiertos de ceniza al sur de la bahía de las nubes. Dada su enorme boca, "
"los gusanos del desierto se alimentan de la arena misma, digiriendo "
"cualquier criatura viva o restos orgánicos que haya dentro. Como tal, a "
"menudo se les llama las «ballenas del desierto». Cuando se acercan a su "
"nido, también se ha visto que los gusanos del desierto devoran a viajeros "
"que no esperaban su presencia."

#. [unit_type], id=Genie, race=genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/genie.cfg:4
msgid "Genie"
msgstr "Genio"

#. [unit_type], id=Genie, race=genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/genie.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Genie are magical beings that inhabited the great deserts even before men "
"arrived. They are innate friendly beings that maintain a good relationship "
"with humans. Genie helped the people of the desert to build their enormous "
"cities. When the Three Kings of K'thar abused the powers of magic, most "
"genie died, since they are susceptible to destructive magic. Only a few have "
"found a safe place - either in manmade objects, such as lamps, swords or "
"jewelry, or in men that agreed to host a genie in their mortal body. United "
"they form the mighty half-genie that are both man and genie. In the land of "
"the deserts, half-genies are not seen as bastards, in fact, they are "
"respected throughout the lands, as their union symbolises the great bond "
"between man and genie that brought forth many good things to the life of "
"both kin. Genie hate Afariyaten more than anything else."
msgstr ""
"Los genios son seres mágicos que habitaban los grandes desiertos incluso "
"antes de que llegaran los hombres. Son seres inherentemente amigables que "
"mantienen una buena relación con los humanos. Los genios ayudaron al pueblo "
"del desierto a construir sus enormes ciudades. Cuando los Tres Reyes de "
"K'thar abusaron de los poderes de la magia, la mayoría de los genios "
"murieron, ya que son susceptibles a la magia destructiva. Solo unos pocos "
"encontraron un lugar seguro, ya sea en objetos hechos por el hombre como "
"lámparas, espadas o joyas, o en hombres que aceptaron albergar a un genio en "
"su cuerpo mortal. Unidos forman los poderosos medio genios que son tanto "
"hombre como genio. En las tierras del desierto, los medio genios no se ven "
"como bastardos, de hecho, son respetados en todas las tierras, ya que su "
"unión simboliza el gran vínculo entre hombre y genio que trajo muchas cosas "
"buenas a la vida de ambos linajes. Los genios odian a los afariyaten más que "
"a nada."

#. [unit_type], id=Genie_Kabir, race=genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/genie_kabir.cfg:4
msgid "Genie-Kabir"
msgstr "Genio-Kabir"

#. [unit_type], id=Genie_Kabir, race=genie
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/genie_kabir.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Genie-Kabir are greater genie that often work to further their races eternal "
"cause to harm and hinder their ancient enemy, the afariyaten. However, "
"unlike their enemies whose only goal in life resides in complete "
"annihilation, the Genie-Kabir are highly interested in maintaining and "
"increasing their friendship with the people of the deserts, the ones that "
"saved them from the destructive magic of the Three Kings. Wielding magical "
"scimitars, they are ready to protect themselves and their allies from any "
"threat to either of them."
msgstr ""
"Los Genio-Kabir son genios mayores que a menudo trabajan para avanzar la "
"causa eterna de su raza de dañar y obstaculizar a su enemigo antiguo, los "
"afariyaten. Sin embargo, a diferencia de sus enemigos cuyo único objetivo en "
"la vida reside en la aniquilación completa, los Genio-Kabir están muy "
"interesados en mantener y aumentar su amistad con el pueblo de los "
"desiertos, aquellos que los salvaron de la magia destructiva de los Tres "
"Reyes. Empuñando cimitarras mágicas, están listos para protegerse a sí "
"mismos y a sus aliados de cualquier amenaza para cualquiera de ellos."

# Sebas:En este caso, según la descripcion de esta unidad considero que GreenScarab es un nombre propio.
#. [unit_type], id=Green Scarab, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/green_scarab.cfg:4
msgid "Green Scarab"
msgstr "Green Scarab"

#. [special_note]
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/green_scarab.cfg:23
msgid ""
"This unit can hide under loose dirt, sand, or leaves, concealing itself if "
"it does not change location."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidad puede esconderse bajo tierra suelta, arena u hojas, ocultándose "
"si no cambia de ubicación."

#. [unit_type], id=Green Scarab, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/green_scarab.cfg:27
msgid ""
"I am GreenScarab and I have created several Wesnoth campaigns: Born to Live, "
"Horn of Faith, Dream in the Sand, Rustling in the Wind, Waves of Distant "
"Shore, Dusk of Dawn and The Cost of Living: New Dawn."
msgstr ""
"Soy GreenScarab y he creado varias campañas de Wesnoth: Born to Live, Horn "
"of Faith, Dream in the Sand, Rustling in the Wind, Waves of Distant Shore, "
"Dusk of Dawn y The Cost of Living: New Dawn."

#. [unit_type], id=Magical Book, race=mechanical
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/magical_book.cfg:4
msgid "Magical Book"
msgstr "Libro Mágico"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/magical_book.cfg:23
msgid "book"
msgstr "libro"

#. [unit_type], id=Magical Scimitar, race=mechanical
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/magical_scimitar.cfg:4
msgid "Magical Scimitar"
msgstr "Cimitarra Mágica"

#. [unit_type], id=Minotaur, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/minotaur.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Minotaurs have the statue of both man and bull and are often found in the "
"eastern parts of the mountainside around Kesh and the eastern flatlands. "
"These strong creatures are occasionally caught and trained for war, but "
"oftentimes catching a minotaur leads to the death of numerous soldiers and "
"hunters, resulting in a loss of valuable manpower to rival the beasts own "
"worth. Thus, the decision to field these unstable creatures is not a matter "
"to be taken lightly and better be thought through thrice."
msgstr ""
"Los minotauros tienen la estatua de hombre y toro y se encuentran a menudo "
"en las partes orientales de las montañas alrededor de Kesh y las llanuras "
"orientales. Estas fuertes criaturas son ocasionalmente capturadas y "
"entrenadas para la guerra, pero a menudo capturar a un minotauro lleva a la "
"muerte de numerosos soldados y cazadores, resultando en una pérdida de mano "
"de obra valiosa que rivaliza con el valor propio de las bestias. Por lo "
"tanto, la decisión de desplegar a estas criaturas inestables no es algo que "
"se tome a la ligera y es mejor pensarlo tres veces."

#. [unit_type], id=Mycorrhian, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/mycorrhian.cfg:4
msgid "Mycorrhian"
msgstr "Micorriano"

#. [unit_type], id=Mycorrhian, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/mycorrhian.cfg:57
msgid ""
"Having dwelled in the darkest depths for eons, they have perfectly adapted "
"to the surroundings. Warning: Do not inhale their spores!"
msgstr ""
"Habiendo habitado en las profundidades más oscuras por eones, se han "
"adaptado perfectamente al entorno. ¡Advertencia: no inhalen sus esporas!"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/mycorrhian.cfg:77
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/mycorrhian.cfg:89
msgid "spore powder"
msgstr "polvo de esporas"

#. [unit_type], id=Najae_snake, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/najae-snake.cfg:4
msgid "Najae-snake"
msgstr "Serpiente Najae"

#. [unit_type], id=Najae_snake, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/najae-snake.cfg:18
msgid ""
"While the bite of the  Najae-Snakes itself is not deadly, the poison that is "
"injected during the bite is known to slowly devour the victim from the "
"inside."
msgstr ""
"Si bien la mordida de las serpientes Najae en sí no es mortal, el veneno que "
"inyectan durante la mordida es conocido por devorar lentamente a la víctima "
"desde adentro."

#. [unit_type], id=Tangshe, race=monster
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/monsters/tangshe.cfg:4
msgid "Tangshe"
msgstr "Tangshe"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Thrall, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/black_thrall.cfg:4
msgid "Black Thrall"
msgstr "Esclavo Negro"

#. [unit_type], id=Black Thrall, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/black_thrall.cfg:24
msgid ""
"An abomination only conceivably worked on by experienced necromancers, the "
"black thrall towers over its master's enemies with a combination of hunger "
"and rage atypical of their creations. Its unusual behaviour and ghoul-like "
"attitude makes even most of their masters fearful of even calling upon their "
"help."
msgstr ""
"Una abominación solo concebiblemente trabajada por nigromantes "
"experimentados, el esclavo negro se eleva sobre los enemigos de su amo con "
"una combinación de hambre y rabia atípica de sus creaciones. Su "
"comportamiento inusual y actitud parecida a un necrófago hace que incluso la "
"mayoría de sus amos teman siquiera invocar su ayuda."

#. [unit_type], id=Iron Thrall, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/iron_thrall.cfg:4
msgid "Iron Thrall"
msgstr "Esclavo de Hierro"

#. [unit_type], id=Iron Thrall, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/iron_thrall.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Although their ever increasing size and suffocating stench of decay hinders "
"their ability to pass as a human in any kind of situation, the iron thrall "
"exibhits enough strengh to be armed with a strong weapon capable of crushing "
"even the most valiant of knights."
msgstr ""
"Aunque su tamaño cada vez mayor y el hedor sofocante de la descomposición "
"dificultan su capacidad de pasar como humano en cualquier situación, el "
"esclavo de hierro exhibe suficiente fuerza para ser armado con un arma "
"fuerte capaz de aplastar incluso al más valiente de los caballeros."

#. [unit_type], id=Mummy, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/mummy.cfg:4
msgid "Mummy"
msgstr "Momia"

#. [unit_type], id=Mummy, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/mummy.cfg:23
msgid ""
"A mummy is the corpse of a fallen warrior whose soul was denied entry to the "
"realm of the dead. Filled with hatred, a mummy then roams the dark places of "
"the desert lands seeking a different way to end their suffering."
msgstr ""
"Una momia es el cadáver de un guerrero caído cuya alma fue denegada la "
"entrada al reino de los muertos. Llena de odio, una momia luego vaga por los "
"lugares oscuros de las tierras del desierto buscando una forma diferente de "
"terminar su sufrimiento."

#. [unit_type], id=Thrall, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/thrall.cfg:4
msgid "Thrall"
msgstr "Esclavo"

#. [unit_type], id=Thrall, race=undead
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/undead/thrall.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The life-like appearance of the thrall can confuse people when seen from "
"afar or in the darkness. Nerverthless, the sighting of its swollen and "
"blackened body reveals his true nature as a creation of an evil mind."
msgstr ""
"La apariencia realista del esclavo puede confundir a la gente cuando se le "
"ve de lejos o en la oscuridad. Sin embargo, la visión de su cuerpo hinchado "
"y ennegrecido revela su verdadera naturaleza como creación de una mente "
"maligna."

#. [unit_type], id=Tropical Ancient Wose, race=wose
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/woses/Tropical_Ancient.cfg:4
msgid "Tropical Ancient Wose"
msgstr "Wose Anciani Tropical"

#. [unit_type], id=Tropical Elder Wose, race=wose
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/woses/Tropical_Elder.cfg:4
msgid "Tropical Elder Wose"
msgstr "Wose Adulto Tropical"

#. [unit_type], id=Tropical Wose, race=wose
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/woses/Tropical_Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Tropical Wose"
msgstr "Wose Tropical"

#. [unit_type], id=Tropical Wose Sapling, race=wose
#: Oath_of_Allegiance_Ref/units/woses/Tropical_Wose_Sapling.cfg:4
msgid "Tropical Wose Sapling"
msgstr "Wose Retoño Tropical"

